Starting the day with the new Tenon Premium desk by @beflodesign 🖥️ Review of the desk is now live on my YouTube channel 😉

I got sponsored a new desk to try out by @beflodesign and I can’t remember my home office desk ever being this tidy.

This is the Tenon Premium and I love how it looks like it’s just a nicely designed, conventional desk—until you raise the height and turn on ambient lighting.

I used to just stick accessories under my desk so having a way to actually store them while remaining accessible is a clever idea.

Docking the MacBook INTO the desk is just… well I’ve never seen anything like it and I think it’s brilliant!

The desk mat is currently my favorite one out of all that I have just because of how thin and soft it feels.

Some wishlist items remain (which I mentioned in my video review on YouTube) but overall, especially for a first product, this hits a lot of the right spots for a premium home office desk.

Would love for you guys to check out the video. I think you’re going to like what you see 😉

Happy Thursday! My morning routine has changed quite a bit in the last month or two. I know it’s going to sound blasphemous but I don’t drink coffee first thing in the morning anymore 😬

I get up, drink a quick protein breakfast (or shake), get the kids ready, take them to school, come home, and workout.

After workout, quick meal, shower, answer emails, create content, then pick up kids.

It’s nice to have a morning that’s more focused on what’s important to me. That’s why I usually start my work day later in the morning.

What’s your routine like? I’d like to know 😊

#AD Not only has this Air Purifier made my life so much better, it actually looks good in my space too!

On levels 1 & 2, the fans run silently which is great when working from home or when you’re asleep. Levels 3 & 4 are very powerful and will definitely remove any dust and pollen floating around.

Built my first mechanical keyboard thanks to @windstudio_offical 🙌🏼

This is the X98, a very premium kit with amazing build quality. My hands are normally completely made out of cheese when it comes to putting things together but this was a very satisfying process from start to finish.

I chose to get the Redsuns GMK Blue Samurai Keycap set by @drop as they looked to be the perfect match for the case.

For the switches I went with the DUROCK Silent Linear Daybreak which is very quiet yet satisfying to type on.

I already ordered a Bluetooth PCB because now I want to use this keyboard in my other setup 😬

To anyone who hasn’t built a mechanical keyboard before, DON’T DO IT unless you’re willing to have a long conversation with yourself as to why your bank account keeps going down 😂

I’ve been using the Smart Lock U100 for at least a month now and it’s my new favorite smart home accessory!

Not having to carry keys when I’m out running is such a big convenience. The U100 can also be set with custom automations so that it recognizes when you’re home or when you’ve left.

It’s integrated so well in HomeKit that I have full confidence knowing if my door is locked or not through my phone.

I’ve even used remote unlocking to let family in when I was away and the Aqara smart home app keeps a log of when the door was locked/unlocked.

There’s a lot more that can be done with this device but it’s already more than what I typically need. More importantly, it works, it’s secure, reliable, and it looks nice. Well done @aqara_smarthome ! Highly recommend.

Showing some of the goodies @pgytechglobal sent that I included in my Tech Bag video (now live on YouTube).

The shoulder bag is part of the OneMo 2 backpack and looks even better in person. Very functional and a lot of thought has gone into designing that bag for creators and filmmakers.

The wrist straps were a really, really nice surprise as I think they are made very well. Great color and materials and the proprietary anchor system is virtually effortless to use. Amazing design.

The Mars 3 by @seenebula is a true portable projector made for the OUTDOORS!

Rugged design, easy to setup, super bright, and great sound. Addition of LED strip in the back is a nice touch and the extended battery life makes this truly an ideal portable projector.

You can even use this as an external battery thanks to reverse charging. Smart!

I gave up my hobby of taking photos of cars a few years ago but finally getting my @acura Integra Type-S has reignited that passion. I mean, look at it!

It has so many interesting lines and the way the light falls on the varying curves are so satisfying to look at. Cars with emotional design are quite rare nowadays which makes this super fun to photograph.

I draw a lot of inspiration from car design which influences the things I surround myself with. It’s a topic I’m working on that I’ll be sharing in a future video.

In the meantime, if you like/love cars, follow my other account @auto_enthused

This is NOT a sponsored post! I’ve been a @rayban fan for years and seeing the new @raybanmeta got me all curious. 

They can record up to 60 seconds of vertical video at 1440x1920 at 30FPS. Photo resolution is higher at 3024X4032

In my testing, battery life is around 3-4hours depending on usage and the case allows up to 8 full recharges. At 11% battery life, I popped the sunglasses in and got 58% in about 12 minutes. Not bad!

Most impressive is the way it looks as they look like normal sunglasses and even the added weight of the tech is negligible. Speakers are not stellar but not terrible either. The microphone pick up is REALLY impressive!

Meta’s own AI for voice command is pretty cool but still has some catching up to do.

These retail for $299 which in my honest opinion, is an awesome price for what they offer. #raybanmeta

I was too excited not to share this Limited Edition 3xt GMT watch by @boldrsupplyco X @wornandwound 

Only been on my wrist for a little less than two days and it just might be my new favorite daily. Chunky case but the 41mm bezel (43mm at its widest point) makes this look much smaller on the wrist.

The Miyota 9075 movement in this makes it a true GMT watch at a more attainable price point.

Sapphire crystal lens and 200M of water resistance makes this such a great adventure watch that’s super fun to wear and look at all day long!
